Class Hierarchy

  • object: The most base type
    • MDSplus.connection.Connection: Implements an MDSip connection to an MDSplus server
    • MDSplus.mdsdata.Data: Superclass used by most MDSplus objects.
      • MDSplus.apd.Apd: The Apd class represents the Array of Pointers to Descriptors structure.
      • MDSplus.mdsarray.Array
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Float32Array: 32-bit floating point number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Float64Array: 64-bit floating point number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Int128Array: 128-bit signed number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Int16Array: 16-bit signed number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Int32Array: 32-bit signed number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Int64Array: 64-bit signed number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Int8Array: 8-bit signed number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.StringArray: String
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Uint128Array: 128-bit unsigned number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Uint16Array: 16-bit unsigned number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Uint32Array: 32-bit unsigned number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Uint64Array: 64-bit unsigned number
        • MDSplus.mdsarray.Uint8Array: 8-bit unsigned number
      • MDSplus.compound.Compound
        • MDSplus.compound.Action: An Action is used for describing an operation to be performed by an MDSplus action server.
        • MDSplus.compound.Call: A Call is used to call routines in shared libraries.
        • MDSplus.compound.Conglom: A Conglom is used at the head of an MDSplus conglomerate.
        • MDSplus.compound.Dependency: A Dependency object is used to describe action dependencies.
        • MDSplus.compound.Dimension: A dimension object is used to describe a signal dimension, typically a time axis.
        • MDSplus.compound.Dispatch: A Dispatch object is used to describe when an where an action should be dispatched to an MDSplus action server.
        • MDSplus.compound.Function: A Function object is used to reference builtin MDSplus functions.
        • MDSplus.compound.Method: A Method object is used to describe an operation to be performed on an MDSplus conglomerate/device
        • MDSplus.compound.Procedure: A Procedure is a deprecated object
        • MDSplus.compound.Program: A Program is a deprecated object
        • MDSplus.compound.Range: A Range describes a ramp.
        • MDSplus.compound.Routine: A Routine is a deprecated object
        • MDSplus.compound.Signal: A Signal is used to describe a measurement, usually time dependent, and associated the data with its independent axis (Dimensions).
        • MDSplus.compound.Window: A Window object can be used to construct a Dimension object.
      • MDSplus.apd.Dictionary: dictionary class
      • MDSplus.mdsdata.EmptyData: No Value
      • MDSplus.ident.Ident: Reference to MDSplus Ken Variable
      • MDSplus.apd.List: list class
        • MDSplus.connection.Connection.GetMany: Build a list of expressions to evaluate
        • MDSplus.connection.Connection.PutMany: Build list of put instructions.
      • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Scalar
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Float32: 32-bit floating point number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Float64: 64-bit floating point number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Int128: 128-bit number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Int16: 16-bit signed number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Int32: 32-bit signed number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Int64: 64-bit signed number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Int8: 8-bit signed number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.String: String
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Uint128: 128-bit unsigned number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Uint16: 16-bit unsigned number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Uint32: 32-bit unsigned number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Uint64: 64-bit unsigned number
        • MDSplus.mdsscalar.Uint8: 8-bit unsigned number
      • MDSplus.treenode.TreeNode: Class to represent an MDSplus node reference (nid).
        • MDSplus.treenode.CachedTreeNode: Node belonging to a cached tree
        • MDSplus.mdsdevice.Device: Used for device support classes.
        • MDSplus.treenode.TreePath: Class to represent an MDSplus node reference (path).
      • MDSplus.treenode.TreeNodeArray
    • MDSplus.tree.Tree: Open an MDSplus Data Storage Hierarchy
      • MDSplus.tree.CachedTree: MDSplus tree with cached data updating
    • threading._Verbose
      • threading.Thread
        • MDSplus.event.Event: Thread to wait for event
    • dict: dict() -> new empty dictionary.
      • MDSplus.apd.Dictionary: dictionary class
    • list: list() -> new list list(sequence) -> new list initialized from sequence's items
      • MDSplus.apd.List: list class
        • MDSplus.connection.Connection.GetMany: Build a list of expressions to evaluate
        • MDSplus.connection.Connection.PutMany: Build list of put instructions.
    • type: type(object) -> the object's type type(name, bases, dict) -> a new type
      • MDSplus.compound.MetaClass
